lexperm
-------
Copyright 2011 (c)
Kouzoupis Antonis <kouzoupis.ant@gmail.com>

About
-----
Generates permutations in lexicographic order.

Usage
-----
lexperm N -- N is the order of the permutation. Generates all the permutations
                of the given order.
lexperm PERMUTATION -- PERMUTATION is a permutation of n order with its digits
                space separated. Generates the next lexicographic permutation.

Examples
--------
lexperm 4 -- Generates all the permutations of order 4 in lexicographic order.
                The number of the permutations is n! so beware of the N.
lexperm 2 4 1 3 -- Generates the next permutation in lexicographic order.

